data.content:
noun
plural -ups
[count] a list of the players who are playing in a game (such as baseball)
The manager has made some changes to the starting lineup. [=the list of players who are playing when the game begins]
the players on such a list
The team has a powerful lineup.
a group of people who are going to perform at an event
the show's star-studded lineup (of performers)
a group of television programs that are shown one after another
tonight's lineup of shows
The networks all had different lineups for the new season.
US :a line of people who stand next to each other while someone tries to identify one of them as the person who has committed a crime
She was asked to pick her attacker out of a lineup. - called also (Brit) identification parade, (Brit) identity parade
